query: Summarize the basic information of the teams that replaced their managers in 2008.
summary: In 2008, 4 teams in the Belgian First Division replaced their managers. Mons replaced Philippe Saint-Jean with Thierry Pister as caretaker on 21 August 2008, as Saint-Jean had resigned. Roeselare replaced Dirk Geeraerd with Dennis Van Wijk on 29 October 2008, as Geeraerd had been sacked. Germinal Beerschot replaced Harm Van Veldhoven with Aimé Anthuenis on 14 November 2008, as Van Veldhoven had resigned. Mons then replaced Pister with Christophe Dessy as caretaker on 4 December, 2008, as Pister had been sacked. Charleroi replaced Thierry Siquet with John Collins on 15 December 2008, as Siquet had been sacked.

query: Summarize the races in which Emanuele Pirro raced in a Lmp900 class car.
summary: Emanuele Pirro raced in three Lmp900 class cars from 2001 to 2003. In 2001, he was part of Audi Sport North America and drove an Audi R8 chassis powered by a 3.6L Turbo V8 engine. He placed first that year with 202 points. The following year, he repeated the same feat and remained with the same team, and vehicle and engine combination but placed fourth this time around with 206 points. In 2003, Pirro raced with Adt Champion Racing, once again in an Audi R8 but this time his efforts only earned him a 18th place rank, totalling 22 points.

table.title: List of tallest buildings in Nagoya - Tallest buildings

query: What are the five tallest buildings in Nagoya and how do their heights compare to each other?
summary: The five tallest buildings in Nagoya are Midland Square, JR Central Office Tower, JR Central Hotel Tower, JR Gate Tower, and JP Tower. Midland Square holds the title of the tallest building in Nagoya, with a height of 247 meters (810 feet), while the JR Central Office Tower is second tall, with a height of 245 meters (804 feet). The height of other three buildings range from 196 meters (642 feet) for JP Tower, 226 meters (741 feet) for JR Central Hotel Tower, and 211 meters (693 feet) for JR Gate Tower. This showing a notice difference in heights among the top five tallest buildings in city.

table.title: Soccer in the United States - FIFA Women's World Cup on TV

query: How has the viewership of FIFA Women's World Cup matches involving the United States changed over the years according to the data provided in the table?
summary: According to the data provided in the table, the viewership of FIFA Women's World Cup matches involving the United States has significantly increased over the years. The 2015 final match between the United States and Japan reached the highest number of viewers with 26.7 million, compared to 18 million in the 1999 final against China PR. Additionally, all three matches involving the United States in the group stage, and knockout stage of the 2015 World Cup had higher viewership numbers than previous years, indicating a growing interest in women's soccer in the country.
